I have been having trouble with inverse address queries using the nameserver.
We are running 4.3-tahoe with bind 4.8.  My question is how is the
in-addr.arpa domain set up with the root servers?

Should each network number have a registered in-addr.arpa record with
the root servers?  This doesn't seem to be the case.  My network number is
129.89.  Locally, if I request an inverse mapping I ask my nameserver for
"host.subnet.89.129.in-addr.arpa." and it returns the name of the host.  If
someone is outside of our domain (89.129.in-addr.arpa.) how does the inverse
mapping work?

Thanks,

--
	- Jim 

